DIALOG | P_NAME | What do you mean?
DIALOG | Wilmer | You see, youngster, `kw`Cuchulainn's`rt` been - `w1`*cough*cough*`w0` - excuse me, got a little somethin' stuck in my windpipes there. 
DIALOG | Wilmer | He's been rounding up the dwarfs all over the galaxy and puttin' most of them in Tir na nOg. 
DIALOG | Wilmer | None of us knows why. Some people say it's because when all the dwarfs are here, he's going to take us to a new place... a better place. I don't know if I believe that, but I don't disbelieve it and it sure sounds nice.
DIALOG | P_NAME | But I don't get it, why is this Cuchulainn guy doing this?
DIALOG | Wilmer | I don't get it either, `w1`*cough*cough*`w0` youngster. But what I do know is that we can't `w1`*cough*`w0` leave. Least not out the front door. Duergars'll stop us. They're his lackeys. 
DIALOG | Wilmer | Some folks say you can get out through `kw`The Sewer System`rt` at the north end of the town, but I think that entire notion is a load of horse patoot. 
